headline.main: YUGOSLAVIA TENSE; Belgrade Fears Spread of War in Balkans Is Inevitable SOFIA ISOLATED 23 HOURS Exit From Bulgarian Capital Barred -- Many Employes of British Arrested

lead_paragraph: BELGRADE, Yugoslavia, Feb. 28 -- An extended war in this part of the world now appears to be virtually inevitable, and possibly very imminent.
abstract: German troops move south from Rumania to Bulgarian border
